column17: Summary provided during digitization: Pre-July 4th, 1976. Host Stacey Ann has a group of callers on the line. They talk about the need for political activism and what they can do during the Bicentennial celebration. "Marry an American" and "Me" from the musical "Boy Meets Boy" play. Over another song from the musical, Stacey Ann gives a positive review of "Boy Meets Boy." "It’s a Dolly," "What Do I Care," and another song from the musical play. "Carey" by Joni Mitchell and "Baby, Take a Bow" play.
